{% doc %}
  @prompt
    breadcrumb for a Shopify metaobject template page where the URL pattern is /pages/crystals/[handle]. The Liquid root object is metaobject — access all fields using dot notation like metaobject.display_name.value.
    
    Layout: A single horizontal row with three zones — left button, center content, right button — using CSS Grid (grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr). On mobile (below 640px), stack into two rows: center content spans full width on top, left and right buttons sit side by side below it.
    
    Left zone: A navigation link styled as a sharp rectangular outlined button (zero border-radius). Shows a left-pointing SVG chevron icon on the left + label text. The chevron is drawn inline as an SVG polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6", stroke currentColor, no fill, stroke-width 2. Links to an editable URL in schema settings.
    
    Center zone: Two stacked elements — (1) a small all-caps tracked label text link (editable in schema, default "VIEW ALL CRYSTALS & MINERALS") linking to the compendium URL, and (2) a breadcrumb trail reading: Home › Crystal Compendium › [metaobject.display_name.value] where Home links to /, Crystal Compendium links to an editable schema URL, and the current entry name is plain non-linked text pulled from metaobject.display_name.value.
    
    Right zone: A navigation link styled identically to the left button but with the chevron on the right pointing right, SVG polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6". Links to an editable URL in schema settings.
    
    Schema settings — all editable in the theme editor sidebar:
    
    Back button label (text, default: "Back to Crystal Compendium")
    Back button URL (url picker)
    Browse More button label (text, default: "Browse More")
    Browse More button URL (url picker)
    Center label text (text, default: "VIEW ALL CRYSTALS & MINERALS")
    Crystal Compendium URL used in breadcrumb and center label (url picker)
    Background color (color, default: #FAF9F7)
    Text color (color, default: #1A1A1A)
    Button border color (color, default: #1A1A1A)
    Accent and hover color (color, default: #0066FF)
    Button border width in px (range 1–4, default: 1)
    Button vertical padding in px (range 8–32, default: 14)
    Button horizontal padding in px (range 16–56, default: 28)
    Section padding top in px (range 0–80, default: 24)
    Section padding bottom in px (range 0–80, default: 24)
    Section max-width in px (range 800–1600, default: 1280)
    Breadcrumb font size in px (range 11–20, default: 14)
    Button label font size in px (range 12–22, default: 16)
    Center label font size in px (range 10–18, default: 13)
    Letter spacing for breadcrumb and center label (range 0–30 stored as integer, divide by 100 in CSS to get em value, default: 12)
    Hover animation style (select: "underline" = sliding bottom border, "fill" = solid background fill, "glow_pulse" = pulsing box-shadow, default: underline)
    Glow effect toggle (checkbox, default: false) — when enabled adds a colored box-shadow on hover
    Glow intensity (select: subtle = 0 0 8px 2px, medium = 0 0 16px 4px, strong = 0 0 28px 8px, default: subtle)
    Entrance animation toggle (checkbox, default: true) — when enabled the section fades up from 18px below on scroll using IntersectionObserver
    Fonts: Import Raleway (weights 300, 400) and Poppins (weights 400, 500) from Google Fonts via @import in the style tag. Use Raleway light (300) for all text throughout. Button labels use font-size from schema. Breadcrumb uses font-size from schema. All text uses the text color from schema.
    
    Button hover states: All three hover styles must change text color and border color to the accent color. If glow is enabled, add box-shadow using the selected intensity value and accent color at 55% opacity. The underline style adds a 2px bottom pseudo-element that slides from width 0 to 100%. The fill style changes background to accent color and text to white. The glow_pulse style adds a CSS keyframe animation alternating box-shadow opacity between 44% and 99%.
    
    Breadcrumb and center label hover: Links change to accent color on hover with a 0.2s ease transition.
    
    Entrance animation: Use IntersectionObserver in a script tag. Set initial state opacity: 0; transform: translateY(18px) via CSS, add class mnav-visible with opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: 0.6s ease when the section enters the viewport. Fall back gracefully if IntersectionObserver is not supported.
    
    Mobile optimization: Below 640px — center content goes full width on its own row above the buttons. Left and right buttons each take 50% width and are justified to their respective edges. Button font size reduces by 2px. Button padding reduces slightly. Breadcrumb wraps and centers. No horizontal overflow.
    
    Style rules: Zero border-radius everywhere. No gradients. No pill shapes. Smooth 0.25s ease transitions on color, border-color, background, box-shadow. Section width 100%. Inner container uses max-width from schema, centered with auto margins, 24px horizontal padding. 
{% enddoc %}
{% assign ai_gen_id = block.id | replace: '_', '' | downcase %}

{% style %}
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Raleway:wght@300;400&family=Poppins:wght@400;500&display=swap');

  .mnav-container-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    background-color: {{ block.settings.background_color }};
    padding-top: {{ block.settings.padding_top }}px;
    padding-bottom: {{ block.settings.padding_bottom }}px;
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(18px);
    transition: opacity 0.6s ease, transform 0.6s ease;
  }

  .mnav-container-{{ ai_gen_id }}.mnav-visible {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }

  .mnav-inner-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    max-width: {{ block.settings.max_width }}px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px;
  }

  .mnav-grid-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 24px;
  }

  .mnav-left-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    justify-self: start;
  }

  .mnav-center-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    justify-self: center;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .mnav-right-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    justify-self: end;
  }

  .mnav-button-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: {{ block.settings.button_padding_vertical }}px {{ block.settings.button_padding_horizontal }}px;
    background-color: transparent;
    color: {{ block.settings.text_color }};
    border: {{ block.settings.button_border_width }}px solid {{ block.settings.button_border_color }};
    border-radius: 0;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: 'Raleway', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: {{ block.settings.button_font_size }}px;
    transition: color 0.25s ease, border-color 0.25s ease, background 0.25s ease, box-shadow 0.25s ease;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .mnav-button-{{ ai_gen_id }} svg {
    width: 16px;
    height: 16px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .mnav-button-{{ ai_gen_id }}:hover {
    color: {{ block.settings.accent_color }};
    border-color: {{ block.settings.accent_color }};
  }

  {% if block.settings.hover_style == 'underline' %}
    .mnav-button-{{ ai_gen_id }}::after {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 0;
      height: 2px;
      background-color: {{ block.settings.accent_color }};
      transition: width 0.25s ease;
    }

    .mnav-button-{{ ai_gen_id }}:hover::after {
      width: 100%;
    }
  {% elsif block.settings.hover_style == 'fill' %}
    .mnav-button-{{ ai_gen_id }}:hover {
      background-color: {{ block.settings.accent_color }};
      color: #ffffff;
    }
  {% elsif block.settings.hover_style == 'glow_pulse' %}
    @keyframes mnav-glow-pulse-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      0%, 100% {
        box-shadow: {% if block.settings.glow_intensity == 'subtle' %}0 0 8px 2px{% elsif block.settings.glow_intensity == 'medium' %}0 0 16px 4px{% else %}0 0 28px 8px{% endif %} {{ block.settings.accent_color | color_modify: 'alpha', 0.44 }};
      }
      50% {
        box-shadow: {% if block.settings.glow_intensity == 'subtle' %}0 0 8px 2px{% elsif block.settings.glow_intensity == 'medium' %}0 0 16px 4px{% else %}0 0 28px 8px{% endif %} {{ block.settings.accent_color | color_modify: 'alpha', 0.99 }};
      }
    }

    .mnav-button-{{ ai_gen_id }}:hover {
      animation: mnav-glow-pulse-{{ ai_gen_id }} 1.5s ease-in-out infinite;
    }
  {% endif %}

  {% if block.settings.enable_glow %}
    .mnav-button-{{ ai_gen_id }}:hover {
      box-shadow: {% if block.settings.glow_intensity == 'subtle' %}0 0 8px 2px{% elsif block.settings.glow_intensity == 'medium' %}0 0 16px 4px{% else %}0 0 28px 8px{% endif %} {{ block.settings.accent_color | color_modify: 'alpha', 0.55 }};
    }
  {% endif %}

  .mnav-center-label-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Raleway', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: {{ block.settings.center_label_font_size }}px;
    letter-spacing: {{ block.settings.letter_spacing | divided_by: 100.0 }}em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .mnav-center-label-{{ ai_gen_id }} a {
    color: {{ block.settings.text_color }};
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .mnav-center-label-{{ ai_gen_id }} a:hover {
    color: {{ block.settings.accent_color }};
  }

  .mnav-breadcrumb-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-family: 'Raleway', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: {{ block.settings.breadcrumb_font_size }}px;
    letter-spacing: {{ block.settings.letter_spacing | divided_by: 100.0 }}em;
    color: {{ block.settings.text_color }};
  }

  .mnav-breadcrumb-{{ ai_gen_id }} a {
    color: {{ block.settings.text_color }};
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .mnav-breadcrumb-{{ ai_gen_id }} a:hover {
    color: {{ block.settings.accent_color }};
  }

  .mnav-breadcrumb-{{ ai_gen_id }} span {
    margin: 0 6px;
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 640px) {
    .mnav-grid-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      grid-template-rows: auto auto;
      gap: 16px;
    }

    .mnav-center-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      grid-row: 1;
      grid-column: 1;
      width: 100%;
    }

    .mnav-left-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      grid-row: 2;
      grid-column: 1;
      justify-self: start;
      width: 50%;
    }

    .mnav-right-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      grid-row: 2;
      grid-column: 1;
      justify-self: end;
      width: 50%;
    }

    .mnav-button-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.button_font_size | minus: 2 }}px;
      padding: {{ block.settings.button_padding_vertical | minus: 2 }}px {{ block.settings.button_padding_horizontal | minus: 4 }}px;
    }

    .mnav-breadcrumb-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
{% endstyle %}

<metaobject-breadcrumb-{{ ai_gen_id }}
  class="mnav-container-{{ ai_gen_id }} {% unless block.settings.enable_entrance_animation %}mnav-visible{% endunless %}"
  {{ block.shopify_attributes }}
>
  <div class="mnav-inner-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
    <div class="mnav-grid-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
      <div class="mnav-left-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
        {% if block.settings.back_button_url != blank %}
          <a href="{{ block.settings.back_button_url }}" class="mnav-button-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"></polyline>
            </svg>
            <span>{{ block.settings.back_button_label }}</span>
          </a>
        {% endif %}
      </div>

      <div class="mnav-center-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
        {% if block.settings.center_label_text != blank %}
          <div class="mnav-center-label-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
            {% if block.settings.compendium_url != blank %}
              <a href="{{ block.settings.compendium_url }}">{{ block.settings.center_label_text }}</a>
            {% else %}
              {{ block.settings.center_label_text }}
            {% endif %}
          </div>
        {% endif %}
        <nav class="mnav-breadcrumb-{{ ai_gen_id }}" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
          {% if block.settings.compendium_url != blank %}
            <a href="{{ block.settings.compendium_url }}">Crystal Compendium</a>
          {% else %}
            <span>Crystal Compendium</span>
          {% endif %}
          <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
          <span>{{ metaobject.display_name.value }}</span>
        </nav>
      </div>

      <div class="mnav-right-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
        {% if block.settings.browse_more_url != blank %}
          <a href="{{ block.settings.browse_more_url }}" class="mnav-button-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
            <span>{{ block.settings.browse_more_label }}</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"></polyline>
            </svg>
          </a>
        {% endif %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</metaobject-breadcrumb-{{ ai_gen_id }}>

<script>
  (function() {
    class MetaobjectBreadcrumb{{ ai_gen_id }} extends HTMLElement {
      constructor() {
        super();
      }

      connectedCallback() {
        {% if block.settings.enable_entrance_animation %}
          if ('IntersectionObserver' in window) {
            this.setupIntersectionObserver();
          } else {
            this.classList.add('mnav-visible');
          }
        {% endif %}
      }

      setupIntersectionObserver() {
        const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
          entries.forEach((entry) => {
            if (entry.isIntersecting) {
              entry.target.classList.add('mnav-visible');
              observer.unobserve(entry.target);
            }
          });
        }, {
          threshold: 0.1,
          rootMargin: '0px 0px -50px 0px'
        });

        observer.observe(this);
      }
    }

    customElements.define('metaobject-breadcrumb-{{ ai_gen_id }}', MetaobjectBreadcrumb{{ ai_gen_id }});
  })();
</script>

